text:
Waterloo West emerges victorious over Waterloo East Posted: Friday Night Heroes Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> 
East meets West tonight at Memorial Stadium in Waterloo. The winless Trojans meet the 2-3 Wahawks. 
The Wahawks are looking to bounce back from a loss to Cedar Falls last week.. 
West High starts fast tonight--already ahead 7-0 in the first quarter... Wahawk quarterback Devon Moore fires a 28 yard touchdown pass to Jin-Kali. Burt who makes a great catch in the endzone...to make it a 15-0 Wahawk lead ...Burt says the Wahawks are number one...and they probably are in Waterloo. 
In the second quarter--Devon Moore dumps a little screen pass to John Draine--he scampers 25 yards for an apparent touchdown but it is called back for illegal block downfield.. 
No problem ---John Draine races 15 yards to the two yard line... And two plays later Devon oore stretches across to the goal line to give west a 22-0 lead...and West wins the rivalry game 50-13. Can't Find Something? 500 Fourth St. Waterloo, IA 50703 News: (319) 291-1200
